<TITLE> Amazon to become Lovefilm's largest shareholder </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Feb 4 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Online DVD rental business Lovefilm International is to acquire Amazon's DVD rental arm in Britain and Germany in a deal that will make Amazon its largest shareholder. As part of the deal announced on Monday, Amazon Europe will also make an undisclosed cash investment while its Web sites for Britain and Germany will promote Lovefilm's services in a multi-year marketing agreement. The Lovefilm subscriber base will be more than 900,000 following completion of the deal in Britain, Germany, Sweden, Norway and Denmark, the two companies said. The agreement is subject to regulatory approval in the UK and Germany. Online DVD rental companies allow consumers to choose movies on the Web and receive them in the post for a monthly subscription charge. Lovefilm International, formed in 2006, also offers a fast-growing film download service in Britain which it plans to roll out to other countries. "As one of Europe's largest online DVD rental businesses, Lovefilm is well established to serve customers' increasing demand for entertainment," Greg Greeley, Amazon's vice president of European retail, said in a statement. "Our investment will enable Lovefilm to grow the business further and we are excited to be part of their futur
